# Selecting clusters that are needed 
TrainClust <- ClusterTrain %>% select(c(Clus1_physical,Clus1_social,Clus1_psychological,Clus1_demo,Clus1_school,SelfPerceivedHealth))

Random Forest

# Initializing Random Forest
forest_modelClust <- train(
  SelfPerceivedHealth ~ ., 
  data = TrainClust,
  method = "rf",
  tuneGrid = data.frame(mtry = c(1,2,3,5)),
  trControl = trainControl(method = "oob"),
  metric = "Accuracy",
  na.action = na.omit)
forest_modelClust3 <- train(
  SelfPerceivedHealth ~ Clus1_physical + Clus1_social + Clus1_psychological, 
  data = TrainClust,
  method = "rf",
  tuneGrid = data.frame(mtry = c(1,2,3)),
  trControl = trainControl(method = "oob"),
  metric = "Accuracy",
  na.action = na.omit)

## Get variable importance, and turn into a data frame
var_impClust <- varImp(forest_modelClust, scale=FALSE)$importance
var_impClust <- data.frame(variables=row.names(var_impClust), importance=var_impClust$Overall)
var_impClust %>% arrange(desc(importance))
##             variables importance
## 1      Clus1_physical   2561.045
## 2        Clus1_social   2554.392
## 3 Clus1_psychological   2547.813
## 4        Clus1_school   2528.915
## 5          Clus1_demo   1701.598
## Create a plot of variable importance
var_impClust <- var_impClust %>%
  arrange(importance) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=reorder(variables, importance), y=importance)) + 
  geom_bar(stat='identity', fill = "cornflowerblue") + 
  coord_flip() + 
  xlab('Variables') +
  labs(title='Random Forest Variable Importance') + ylab("Gini Impurity") + 
  theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 12), 
        axis.title = element_text(size = 14))

## Generate predictions
y_hatsClust <- predict(
  object=forest_modelClust, 
  newdata= ClusterTest %>% select(-SelfPerceivedHealth,-P28))

## Print the accuracy
accuracy <- mean(y_hatsClust == ClusterTest$SelfPerceivedHealth)*100
cat('Accuracy on testing data: ', round(accuracy, 2), '%',  sep='')
## Accuracy on testing data: 60.41%

## Generate predictions
y_hatsAll <- predict(
  object=forest_modelAll, 
  newdata= Test %>% select(-SelfPerceivedHealth,-P28))

## Print the accuracy
accuracy <- mean(y_hatsAll == Test$SelfPerceivedHealth)*100
cat('Accuracy on testing data: ', round(accuracy, 2), '%',  sep='')
